## 1. Definitions

**"Software"** means the Faion Network source code, documentation, and associated files.

**"Non-commercial use"** means use by individuals for personal projects, use for educational purposes, use for academic research, use by registered non-profit organizations (501(c)(3) or equivalent), and use in open-source projects that are not owned or controlled by for-profit entities.

**"Commercial use"** means any use intended for or directed toward commercial advantage or monetary compensation, including but not limited to:
- Use in products or services sold for profit
- Use by for-profit organizations in any environment (development, staging, production)
- Use in consulting, contracting, or freelance work for paying clients
- Integration into commercial software, SaaS products, or paid services
- Use by employees or contractors on behalf of a for-profit entity

**"Evaluation period"** means a maximum of 30 days for commercial entities to evaluate the Software before obtaining a commercial license.

